                <strong>1. Upper Lake</strong>
                <p>The Upper Lake, also known as Bhojtal, is a scenic lake in Bhopal. It is the largest artificial lake in Asia and offers opportunities for boating and water sports. The lake is surrounded by lush greenery, making it a popular spot for picnics and leisurely walks.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>2. Taj-ul-Masjid</strong>
                <p>Taj-ul-Masjid is one of the largest mosques in India and an important religious landmark in Bhopal. It features stunning architecture with intricate domes, minarets, and marble flooring. Visitors can explore the mosque's peaceful surroundings and admire its grandeur.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>3. Bhimbetka Caves</strong>
                <p>The Bhimbetka Caves are a UNESCO World Heritage Site known for their ancient rock paintings. These caves showcase prehistoric art dating back thousands of years, depicting scenes from the lives of early humans. Exploring the caves offers a fascinating glimpse into India's rich cultural history.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>4. Indira Gandhi Rashtriya Manav Sangrahalaya</strong>
                <p>The Indira Gandhi Rashtriya Manav Sangrahalaya, also known as the National Museum of Humankind, is a unique museum that showcases the diversity of Indian culture and tribal communities. It features exhibits highlighting tribal art, artifacts, and lifestyle, offering an immersive cultural experience.</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
        
